17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4101 of Title 69, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall erect
21 signage designating the following roads as the True Grit Trail:
22 beginning at U.S. Highway 64 at the Oklahoma-Arkansas state line to
23 U.S. Highway 59; from U.S. Highway 59 to U.S. Highway 271; from U.S.
24 Highway 271 to the town of Spiro; from Spiro back to U.S. Highway
