1 11. Robbers Cave State Park;
2 12. The town of Red Oak;
3 13. The town of Bengal;
4 14. The town of Talihina; and
5 15. The Talimena National Scenic Byway.
6 C. The Department of Transportation shall collaborate with the
7 Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department to maintain online
8 resources for the True Grit Trail, including, but not limited to:
9 1. A map of the True Grit Trail;
10 2. Information about each site of significant interest
11 identified in this act; and
12 3. Historical context regarding the True Grit Trail.
13 D. The cost associated with signage required by this act shall
14 be funded from private sources and may include the cost of the
15 initial erection of signs as well as the cost of potential
16 replacement or reconstruction of signs. Upon receiving adequate
17 funding, the Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
18 permanent markers to be placed as required by this act.
19 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
